            "answer_text": "Nullius in Verba Mathematics and Sciences (MS) vs. Humanities (HM) 1. Break a well-established law in MS, and you shall receive a business class ticket to Sweden to receive your Nobel Prize. Break a well-established law in HM, and you shall be dragged and mocked and roasted on twitter and elsewhere and maybe (in the worst-case scenario) you\u2019ll land in jail. 2. MS feels complicated to a beginner, relatively easier to an adept. HM feels easier to a beginner, chaotic and confusing and a constant itch to an adept. 3. If a person pursuing MS discovers a gem, she will most probably go crazy. If a person pursuing HM discovers a gem, she will probably feel proud and satisfied (notice the frenzy-less-ness). 4. A new idea in MS is always welcome, by all (with exception of a few) A new idea in HM is partly accepted, partly rejected, partly mocked, partly cursed, partly celebrated and so (it is a big world). 5. Pick a random page in an MS book and you\u2019ll understand nothing. It is inaccessible to laymen. Pick a random page in an HM book and you\u2019ll understand the thing. It is accessible. 6. MS topics mostly don\u2019t have a human touch. They feel dry and barren and heartless. HM topics are full of human warmth. They are drenched in emotions, full of life, and throbbing hearts everywhere. 7. You can\u2019t survive MS without people around for a long time. Our nature craves for human presence around unless you are a robot. You CAN survive long stretches of complete solitude with books and stuff on HM. 8. MS offers mechanical growth. HM offers natural maturity. 9. MS give chronic exhilaration. HM give smooth joy. 10. In MS, a controversy is mostly accompanied by relentless worldwide efforts to subdue the controversy. And this subduing often happens in one masterstroke. In HM, a controversy is commonplace. Often debated without a conclusion. Often ignored. Often people move on with life. Efforts to subdue it is often accompanied by more conflict and more controversy. In short, HM is controversial without controversy. CONCLUSION? Both are beautiful. Both are hard. Do you want to decide which to choose? Patience with hard math (which may feel meaningless at times) is necessary for MS. HM will mostly try to distract you. Be unmoved. That will aid. A really courageous heart will be an aid in HM. Facing public humiliation while you present your opinion is not so easy. A submissive life will try to distract you. Be unmoved. But be flexible as well. That will aid. ",
