            "answer_text": "Nope. I\u2019m currently in 12th grade and humanities is pretty tough. I have chosen History, Political Science, Economics and Legal Studies. History is mind boggling unless you keep skimming the chapters daily. You are expected to write essays in your answers (I\u2019m referring to the 8 markers) with detailed description, taking reference from sources with neat points and underlined subheadings. History is no joke. We have projects too, in all the subjects. Political Science is not a bed of roses either. It requires a lot of dedication, hard work and persistence. Contemporary International Politics is slightly easier than Indian politics because the chapters are comparatively shorter. In 11th grade, Constitution and Political philosophy are pretty challenging. If you are really passionate about your subjects, you won\u2019t really find anything difficult. Also, subjects like history, political science, economics are extremely interesting. It\u2019s worth it, trust me. ",
